29/09/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Thursday (28 September) rejected an offer for a ceasefire from Abdullah Ocalan, the jailed leader of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK).
Erdogan said a ceasefire cannot be negotiated with a terrorist organisation.
He insisted that the PKK lay down its weapons.
In other news, the governor of the Turkish province of Tunceli confirmed on Thursday that his son was kidnapped.
Serdar Suroglu was driving towards the provincial capital Sunday when PKK members stopped his car.
(AFP - 29/09/06;
Reuters - 28/09/06)
